# Project Rules: LangChain RAG Application

> Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline built with LangChain, Python, and vector databases.

## Project Identity

- **Type**: AI/ML Application (RAG)
- **Language**: Python 3.11+
- **Framework**: LangChain / LangGraph
- **Vector DB**: ChromaDB / Pinecone / Weaviate
- **LLM**: OpenAI / Anthropic / Local (Ollama)
- **Testing**: Pytest + LangSmith (tracing)

---

## Coding Standards

### Naming Conventions

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| Chains | snake_case with `_chain` suffix | `retrieval_chain.py` |
| Prompts | snake_case with `_prompt` suffix | `summarize_prompt.py` |
| Tools | snake_case with `_tool` suffix | `search_tool.py` |
| Modules | snake_case | `document_loader.py` |
| Config | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `OPENAI_API_KEY` |

### File Organization

```
src/
├── chains/            # LangChain chain definitions
│   ├── retrieval.py
│   └── conversational.py
├── prompts/           # Prompt templates
│   ├── system.py
│   └── templates/     # Jinja2 / YAML prompts
├── tools/             # Custom LangChain tools
├── loaders/           # Document loaders & splitters
├── vectorstore/       # Vector DB setup & management
├── agents/            # LangGraph agent definitions
├── evaluation/        # RAG evaluation metrics
├── config/            # Settings & environment
└── utils/             # Shared utilities
data/
├── raw/               # Original documents
├── processed/         # Chunked & embedded data
└── evaluation/        # Test datasets
```

---

## Critical Rules (🔴)

### Rule 1: ❌ Never hardcode API keys or model names

```python
# ❌ BAD — hardcoded
llm = ChatOpenAI(api_key="sk-...", model="gpt-4")

# ✅ GOOD — configurable
from config import settings
llm = ChatOpenAI(
    api_key=settings.OPENAI_API_KEY,
    model=settings.LLM_MODEL,
)
```

### Rule 2: ✅ Always version your prompts

```python
# ❌ BAD — inline prompt, no versioning
response = llm.invoke("Summarize this document: {doc}")

# ✅ GOOD — versioned prompt template
SUMMARIZE_PROMPT_V2 = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([
    ("system", "You are a document summarizer. Be concise and factual."),
    ("human", "Summarize this document:\n\n{document}\n\nKey points only."),
])
```

### Rule 3: ✅ Always implement chunk overlap in text splitting

```python
# ❌ BAD — no overlap, context lost at boundaries
splitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(chunk_size=1000)

# ✅ GOOD — overlap preserves context
splitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(
    chunk_size=1000,
    chunk_overlap=200,
    separators=["\n\n", "\n", ". ", " "],
)
```

---

## Important Guidelines (🟠)

- Use LangSmith for tracing and debugging chains
- Implement RAG evaluation metrics (faithfulness, relevance, recall)
- Cache embeddings to reduce API costs
- Use streaming for long-running LLM calls
- Log token usage and costs per request

---

## Code Smells to Avoid

| ❌ Smell | ✅ Instead Do |
|----------|--------------|
| No evaluation metrics | Implement RAGAS or custom eval |
| Single giant prompt | Break into modular prompt templates |
| No document metadata | Always preserve source, page, date |
| Ignoring retriever scores | Filter by relevance threshold |
| No rate limiting | Implement backoff and retry logic |
